result.name: Coffee Talks

reviews.text: Nice renovation except that there is only one toilet for both sex. Service is fine and the drinks are normal. Just that the price is not as competitive. We came here for 4 drinks and 2 of them are good. The latte was just soso. Good to stay for a bill to chill

Previously I wrote a very positive review of this place. Over the months and many more repeated visits  I regret to say the quality of food and service have gone downhill. The menu hasn't changed at all, yet the service is getting less friendly. They are not happy if you are dining in there for too long, tricks like keep coming to ask what else you like to order,  and constantly come round to clear the table,  put you in an uncomfortable mood. It is a great shame, as I thought I could use this place more often for mentored coffee breaks and gatherings.
Good food, but sadly coffee needs to be improved.  Should take coffee more seriously, cos it is called Coffee Talks, right?

Coffee Talks - a hearty little cafe at Mong Kok, cozy and warm with friendly service.  You can choose to sit either at the comfy sofa dining area or the counter by the window.

Egg Benedict Premium Beef Burger (HK$168)
A classic BLT burger with an egg Benedict on top, how irresistible it is!
The hollandaise sauce that we chose went perfectly with the egg benedict, it was rich and decadent, paired with bacon, lettuce, tomato and a cheesy beef patty, it really made me drool!
There’s four sauce selections for the burger: Traditional Hollandaise, Black Truffle, Beetroot and Avocado Cream Cheese.
The burger set also came with French fries and veggie salad.

Smoked Salmon & Avocado Eggs Benedict (HK$98)
Poached egg over salmon and avocado, Bathed in buttery rich hollandaise sauce and served atop English muffins.  The eggs were cooked to a wonderfully runny consistencies, and the savoury salmon, creamy avocado and the hollandaise sauce made the dish “wow”!

Latte (HK$26)
Original price $36, for any main course order, you can enjoy any drink with $10 discount.

Cappuccino (HK$26)
It’s creamy and the foam was delightful airy!
Nice hidden coffee getaway at the edge of Prince Edward.
